  "original_title": "\u2019\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc2\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Battalantha Ranil failed to prove'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Instead of using emergency law to quell the violence, the government is re-igniting violence in the country by launching mass protests, said ruling party MP Dylan Perera.",
        "He said the above while addressing a special press conference held in Colombo today (28).",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe got an opportunity in Parliament yesterday (27) to prove that he is not in Thailand by forming an all-party government that the people of the country demanded without using the emergency law, even though he came through the back door and became the president in the wrong way. However, he missed it.",
        "The protesters did not demand that the youth be arrested using the Emergency Act. There will be no shortage of fuel, fertilizer or queues in the country due to the declaration of Emergency. Can the international community help a country that has declared a state of emergency? Is IMF assistance available? Dylan Perera MP also raised a question.",
        "Legal action should be taken against those who set fire to the houses of the members of Parliament and those who attacked the empty-faced protestors on May 09. Normal laws in the country are enough for that. Punish those who entered the President's House and send the one who robbed the Central Bank to the President's House? He said that people are asking questions."
      ],
